# California Jack

A 2-player trick-taking card game implemented with Python and Pygame.

## About

California Jack is a classic 2-player card game where players compete to capture valuable trump cards. This implementation provides a graphical interface for playing the game locally (hot-seat multiplayer).

## Current Status

**Version**: CALJACK-003 (Trick-Taking)

This release includes:
- ✅ Main menu with New Game and Help options
- ✅ State management system for screen navigation
- ✅ Card dealing and initial game setup (CALJACK-002)
- ✅ Trick-taking mechanics (CALJACK-003)
- 🔜 Scoring system (CALJACK-004)
- 🔜 Win condition (CALJACK-005)
- 🔜 Help screen with rules (CALJACK-006)
- 🔜 Display last won trick (CALJACK-007)

## Requirements

- Python 3.10+
- Pygame 2.5+

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Brentster311/Golazo-Copilots.git
   cd Golazo-Copilots/PythonApplication2/PythonApplication2
   ```

2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

## Usage

### Running the Game

```bash
python main.py
```

### Controls

- **Mouse**: Click buttons to navigate
- **Close Button (X)**: Exit the game

### Main Menu

From the main menu you can:
- **New Game**: Start a new game with dealt cards
- **Help**: View game rules (placeholder)

### Game Screen

When you start a new game:
- **Your Hand**: 6 cards displayed face-up at the bottom - click to play
- **Opponent's Hand**: 6 cards displayed face-down at the top
- **Stock Pile**: Remaining cards with top card visible (left side)
- **Trump Indicator**: Shows the trump suit (right side)
- **Play Area**: Center shows current trick in progress
- **Turn Indicator**: Shows whose turn it is

### How to Play

1. **Click a card** in your hand to play it
2. **Follow suit** if you can (card turns red if invalid)
3. **Watch the AI** play its card
4. **Trick resolves** after 1 second - winner takes both cards
5. **Draw cards** from stock (winner draws first)
6. **Continue** until all 52 cards are played

## Development

### Running Tests

```bash
pip install pytest
python -m pytest tests/ -v
```

### Project Structure

```
PythonApplication2/
├── main.py                 # Entry point
├── requirements.txt        # Dependencies
├── pytest.ini              # Test configuration
├── game/
│   ├── constants.py        # Window size, colors, state names
│   ├── state_manager.py    # State machine for screen navigation
│   ├── models/
│   │   ├── card.py         # Card dataclass (suit, rank, values)
│   │   ├── deck.py         # Deck class (shuffle, deal, draw)
│   │   ├── trick.py        # Trick model for trick-taking
│   │   └── california_jack.py  # Game state model
│   ├── states/
│   │   ├── base_state.py   # Abstract state interface
│   │   ├── menu_state.py   # Main menu screen
│   │   ├── game_state.py   # Game screen with trick-taking
│   │   ├── help_state.py   # Help screen (placeholder)
│   │   └── placeholder_state.py  # Base for placeholder screens
│   └── ui/
│       ├── button.py       # Reusable button component
│       └── card_renderer.py # Programmatic card rendering
└── tests/
    ├── test_card.py        # Card model tests
    ├── test_deck.py        # Deck model tests
    ├── test_trick.py       # Trick-taking tests
    ├── test_game_state_model.py  # Game state tests
    ├── test_constants.py
    ├── test_menu_state.py
    └── test_state_manager.py
```

## Game Rules (Preview)

California Jack will follow the classic rules:

### Objective
First player to 10 points wins.

### Scoring (per hand)
- **High**: Ace of trumps (1 point)
- **Low**: 2 of trumps (1 point)  
- **Jack**: Jack of trumps (1 point)
- **Game**: Most counting card points (1 point)

### Card Values (for "Game" point)
- 10 = 10 points
- Ace = 4 points
- King = 3 points
- Queen = 2 points
- Jack = 1 point

For complete rules, see [Bicycle Cards - California Jack](https://bicyclecards.com/how-to-play/california-jack/).

